-- Exclusive: Brazil's Vale says signs accord to quit Argentine Potash project
-- By Sabrina Lorenzi
-- Fri Apr 26, 2013 7:17pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2013/04/26/us-vale-riocolorado-idUSBRE93P1BL20130426

 

 RIO DE JANEIRO  (Reuters) - Brazilian global miner Vale SA signed an accord with the Argentine government to leave the $6 billion Rio Colorado potash mining project where it suspended work in December, a company press spokeswoman told Reuters on Friday. 
 (Reporting by Sabrina Lorenzi.; Writing by Jeb Blount; Editing by  Gary Hill )